\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 No. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Well when we\rquote d all finished. Not she at a time. When we\rquote d finished we\rquote 
d finished and then - mother began clearing up the things then we left the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Not just when you had finished yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
If you wanted something passed to you, the salt or something, could you ask for it to be passed to you or did you have to wait until somebody offered it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no, no, you just ask for it be passed round because some of them probably touched the cruet - I don\rquote 
t think we touched the cruet much as children. Mother used to flavour everything sufficiently. I think that\rquote s where the cooking is spoiled a lot these days that - they don\rquote t season the things in the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you have sauces and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you all have your set places at meals, did you always have one particular chain
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you all sit at the same table for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 No one was sort of dotted round the room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
No. No, we had - we had what we called a back kitchen, we - my mother had a Larbrook range, she used to cook all the food there and we had a table there and a form along by the wal
l. We had our dinner there and - and then se used to let that fire out in the afternoon and then light - we had a very large, well, I suppose a room almost large as this, we used to call that the front kitchen. And there was a huge table there, well we co
uld seat twenty in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did she serve the food or did you girls when you were older or how was the meal actually served up, could you describe it to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Well mother used to put - the - usually if it was stews or pudding she had the huge dish, she\rquote 
d turn it onto the table and the vegetable dishes. You had it served up properly, not on your plates. You had the dish and - and she would stand there and serve it out. She served the vegetables for you. She had the vegetables and the dish right beside 
her and then she served out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 If there was a joint who did the carving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
My mother. My father never carved and I remember - my mother was ill and I was about seventeen then and I'd cooked the Sunday dinner and I said to my father, will you carve?
 No, he said, I can't, you get on with it. And I went up and down with this and he said, my goodness, you have made a mess }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3692618\charrsid8939483 of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
 that joint. I said, well you wouldn't try would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did your mother serve the children in a particular order, as you sat or age or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 I think the youngest one came first. My father then the younger one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Your father was the first was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes. I think in those days always the father was first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 When the little ones were too young to feed themselves, when were they fed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
Well mother used - if there was a younger one mother used to have probably a high chair beside her and - she would be feeding the baby probably and herself at the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What about before they were old enough to be in a high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh they were usually fed before. Be fed before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Would she have a child on her lap during a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Never. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Can you remember if your parents brought you up to behave towards your sisters and brothers in certain w
ays, how did they expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Well I think we all agreed that - not with my eldest sister I\rquote m a - I\rquote 
m sorry to say that I have no love for my eldest sister. She\rquote s two years older than me but she had rather a spiteful trait. I don\rquote 
t know where she got it from but - with the younger children, if my mother went out, she would be spiteful to them. And used to quarrel with her quite a lot. Because she was - she was - not nice with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3692618\charrsid8939483 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  younger ones. Oh I was always scrapping with her. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Was your mother aware of this do you think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Well I\rquote , sorry to say that she was the apple of my mother\rquote 
s eye, could do no wrong She was the first you see. She was a very beautiful girl, she was very very attractive, they used to say she
 was worth painting and - and my grandparents rather - they rather spoilt her. She really was the very favoured one but she had this - whether it was because of that, she was made so much of she resented the other children, it may be that but - I was }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3692618\charrsid8939483 always}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  scrapping with her, my mother used to say, you two together again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did your elder sister help the little ones at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, I used to have to do a lot for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did your elder sister help them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 No, I say she had no - no - no - no,
 when - when we were - before my mother died she said to me one day, of all the - of all my girls that should have had children it should have been you, you\rquote 
d have been a wonderful mother. Now she realized that and when she was ill I used to nurse my mother quite a lot and she used to say to me - I don\rquote t know, you should have been a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3692618\charrsid8939483 nurse,}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  she said, you\rquote re so gentle and you\rquote re so - well, placid, she said, you don\rquote t cause any commotion. My other sister younger than me, she said, she\rquote 
s too - you know, sort of - gets all on edge. Yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you help look after the little ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What sort of things did you do for them?
