No, I think my youngest sister when she was born I would be about thirteen - thirteen then. To me she was a live doll. My mother used to say, years after, she said, you mothered her when she was a baby. I did, I was always anxious to get home fro
m school to be with her and - I used to say I\rquote ll put her to bed, bath her, put her to bed and I used to put her in the cot in my mother\rquote s room and I use to lay on my mother\rquote 
s bed singing to her. And then they used to come about nine clock and find me fast asleep on mother\rquote s bed, it was time for me to go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Do you remember if the little girls did anything to help you when you were older, did they do any little jobs for you or errands?
