\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
In West Norwood do you remember some people being talked about as rough, some families being thought of as rough and others as respectable, were you aware of the difference between rough people and respectable people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6555440\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, 
we had - we had - one - one - lad, a family that lived in the road and this boy was very, very cruel, he used to stone a - we used to have a horse that used to be put - cut to graze on this - land and he used to stone that, he - and he had beer known to g
et cats and make a bonfire and burn them, very rough and cruel. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 And my poor grandmother who lived next door, she lost an eye }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6555440\charrsid8939483 
through that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 . She used to stand when they boy - waiting for this - this boy, Marriatt his name was. He had to come down our road, ju
st round the next road he lived and - ooh he was cruel. And my grandmother used to wait for him. Wait to see the boys coming home. To stop them throwing stones at this horse and one day she - this boy was throwing stones and she went - over the field afte
r
 him and there was some boys playing cricket and the cricket ball hit her glasses and she lo-t an eye through it. Now who would think that. Now she was protecting that horse and yet she had to suffer like that. She was in Moorfields hospital for a long ti
me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What was this boy\rquote s family like, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Well - rather rough. But that\rquote 
s the only family I can - think of. We always remember that boy as - he was a terror. I think he finished up in - in a remand home. But there again you know - talking
 of that, we knew - we knew - we knew - a detective. And he was saying about these boys in the old days, especially those that live in the - right in the heart of London. He said that one day he was taking - two boys to a remand home and he said we got ou
t at this station, some little country place, and - he said, we were walking along the road and one boy, said, coo look guv, apples, on a tree. Do they leave them there all night? He said, another time I was going }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  boys and there were chickens running along the road and the boys started chasing off trying to catch one of these chickens. He said, well they don\rquote 
t belong to anybody do they? He said, you know, half of those boys they - they - they didn't know right from wrong. He said, now that boy had never
 seen apples on a tree and he said, do they leave them there all night? As much, you know, guess what was in his mind, I\rquote 
ll be there and they - they had been stealing. He said, with some of them he really felt sorry for, they - they came from homes very poor rough home. He said, you felt sorry for them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 This was the only boy of that sort of type that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 No. Only this boy that was so cruel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 When you were a young girl do you remember hearing anybody described as a real gentleman, w
as it a way people would talk about somebody saying he\rquote s a real gentleman or she\rquote s a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, I\rquote ve heard that but I can\rquote t remember - I\rquote ve heard quite that a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What would people mean if they used that expression?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 A real lady or real gentleman? Well that they respected - they - they had no class distinction. They treated people - on a level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes. You had - you went in fear of them. You were really terrified of a policeman in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did your mother ever say she\rquote d call a policeman if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, many times. The mention of policemen, my word, that was - that was very terrifying. If you saw a policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 How did he treat the people round where you were, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 The police? Oh, with great respect. I can remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you ever feel that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, definitely. Definitely. Every - every penny was laid out, you see, and then - I can remember a very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6555440\charrsid8939483 ,very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
 - hard-up occasion my mother often used to talk about. Now my father, well my parents, they never had anything and I - they never ran up bills. The only tone that was paid weekly was the milkman and the baker. And 
there was a - well always averaged about the same amount you see }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6555440\charrsid8939483 but}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
 that was paid weekly. But - grocery, butchers, everything was on the nail. Well my mother said she remembered an occasion where she was short of tea and - she wasted some tea and she wanted some sugar and she\rquote 
d no money left and the next day was pay day And she went up and was cleaning her bedroom and she found a shilling, when she was cleaning the floor, the - she found a shilling. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6555440\charrsid8939483 
And she said, do you know, that bought me the tea, I think tea was about fourpence a quarter in those days, that bought her tea, sugar and something else, that shilling helped her over. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
And then she mentioned another time. My father had one of these old fashioned - boxes, you know, that used to - letter boxes, w
riting - little miniature writing desks, very old fashioned they are now and - he used to keep, save up his money in this box for our summer holiday and if he - used to put half sovereigns away or a sovereign, something of that. Well apparently he - he
\rquote d saved up fourteen pound in this box and - there was a half sovereign short when he came to - go for his holiday and he said to my mother, have you had any money out of that box? She said, no, I haven\rquote t taken any money she said, there
\rquote s fourteen pounds for a holiday of course that paid for a holiday in those days. And - it\rquote s a funny thing, there was fourteen pound there, there\rquote s a half sovereign missing. Well, she said, I haven\rquote 
t had it. Well that was several years - two or three years after that - from - from then on she\rquote 
d made that box her work box, kept her cottons and needles and all that so he said, oh well we might as well have this for your work box. Well this other occasion, the same day, she was doing some sewing and she - we\rquote d been ill and - and of c
ourse you had doctor\rquote s bills and all that in those days and she\rquote 
d had really a - a rough packet and she was really right down on her beam ends and - and - she had no - no money left in the house. And she was doing this sewing and she said - all of - the bo
x was open - all of a sudden between the - the woodwork you see, she saw something - glitter. Just a fraction of something glittering between the bottom and - and - and this piece of the woodwork. She said it was something glittering there. And - she prob
ed and probed and it was half a sovereign. Now that was that half sovereign had worked under there and been there two or three years. And she said that came - now she said, you know, it made her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6555440\charrsid8939483 believe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  that, you know, that things do happen. Now that was there for a purpose. And - and that half sovereign she found and she said you\rquote 
d all been ill and she said, I\rquote ve had an awfully expensive time and I was really right down with no money in the house. And there was that half }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6555440\charrsid8939483 sovereign}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  came to light. It\rquote s strange isn\rquote t it? And she always used to say - things do turn up for people if they really are deserving and - and - they are down.
