\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you remember as a child being conscious yourself of the fact that they had a struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes. Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What did you think about it, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
We - but we - we never went hungry but - but - they had a struggle. For instance to - I suppose my mother with her money. As I say, I remember the time when she used to take a half a crown out of her ho
usekeeping money to half a family that were probably the husband out of work and a lot of children, we\rquote 
d spend that half a crown and - what we bought for that half a crown used to give them a good meal for the - for the - Sunday. But - we were never - we never went hungry but she used to have a struggle what to do but she used to say, oh something\rquote 
ll turn up. She always believed in that and those two occasions you see, when she was desperately - like that. She always used to relate those.
