\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Do you remember what you felt about the struggle she was having at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 that}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 No, I think we used to just - you know, sort of - feel sorry and wonder - feel sorry for mother and - say oh don\rquote t worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did she show sometimes that she was worrying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, very often. Now for instance, if there were two oranges left, there was eight of us, we used to look at those oranges. She
\rquote d cut them in a quarter, put sugar on them. When you tell children now you - you - you thought a luxury of having a quarter or an 
orange with sugar on, that was a luxury. And we used to suck at it with the skin on you see, with the sugar. But - those - those really were, they were struggling days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Was your father ever ill, did he ever have a period of illness when he had less money or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no, he was a - a Government servant you see. On no, no, no, he was - as a matter of fact I don\rquote 
t remember my father really - being ill. I suppose he was about forty-eight when he had - he had tummy trouble - dyspepsia and he had to go well, on a certain diet you see, not allowed to - to eat certain things. That was the only period I remember.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 He was never out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no. Post Office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 You never got help from anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no. No. My grandmother lived next door but - there again, they - they weren\rquote 
t - too well off I know very often my grandmother used to pass one or two little bits and pieces over to us but - she used to say to mother, she said, I can\rquote t do much for the grandchildren because, she said,
 we have - we have no pension at the end she said, and we have to save for our old age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Could you tell me again about how you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 thought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  the police treated the people around West Norwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 About the people? Oh the policeman? Oh no, the policeman, I think they were very - very kind. - Now you talking of that, there\rquote 
s another thing I remember. Mother only had to say, oh well, I - I shall fetch a policeman, you see if you were naughty. And - and the word policeman, you knew the police, that - they were 
the law. And you were really frightened to do anything wrong, if you saw a policeman you were on - on your best behaviour walking along the road, was a policeman coming and - no, I think the police were very nice and very kind. Now this brought this back 
to me the other day. When my sister, the one that has these four sons, when her - third son was born I was over there one day looking after the children, I\rquote d gone for the day and John, he was about two years old, he was naughty. And he\rquote 
d been to the sideboard and he - he\rquote d taken the sugar and the jam and he had a bottle of cough mixture you know, he\rquote d opened that and he\rquote 
d been drinking, was all smothered in it. I said, oh, you are - just as the doctor came in - I said, you are a naughty boy, I said, I shall have to fetch a policeman to you. The doctor said, don\rquote t you frighten - oh he\rquote 
s a gruff old doctor - don\rquote t you frighten, he said, that child, telling you\rquote ll fetch a policeman. He said, a policeman and a doctor is a child\rquote s best friend. How true that is. My
 - my sister heard that and she always reminds me about that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 You said your home was rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes, fifty-six years we rented that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you know your landlord personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, yes. Tyson I think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15809763\charrsid8939483 her name }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 was and we used to have the 
