\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 ing and then my other sister was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14708622 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  and not very happy in a flat so he said, oh well - of course he
\rquote d got a better position as we\rquote d
 grown up you see and - he gave them a hundred pounds for the ten percent, you got a house for a thousand pounds then, hundred pounds, put down the ten percent deposit. Now he changed his mind about it but he would never go in for a house. My mother begge
d him to try and get our own house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Was that your first husband or Mr Chambers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Mr Chambers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 You never saw the landlord himself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, we did see him sometimes.
