Oh I - I was never late but - if - if there was - the thoughts of being late we used to say, oh just take a note, I shall be late, I shall be late, but anyhow, I we used to 
manage to - scrap in, mother probably wanted something fetched you know for dinner and all - all - go and get this. Oh I shall be late for school. You were really terrified of being late for school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 You said you\rquote d have to take a note, you had to get your mother to write one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes, to know that you had not - that it was really - her fault.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 How did the teachers expect you to behave towards them in your manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh you had to be - they - they were somebody. You had to look up to them. As a
 matter of fact I think that - that the teachers, you were really - you were really scared to do anything wrong. There were one or two exceptions where, you know, they were nice but - as I say, I think the outstanding one of my schooldays was dear old Mrs
 Selby, the headmistress of the girls. Every }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15809763\charrsid8939483 girl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  loved her. She had that gentle manner with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did they go on much about tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes. Yes. And we used to get - we used to get inspectors coming in in those days, I don\rquote t know whether they d
o it now, general knowledge questions. Well I - you know, sort of catching you and - I remember one day, the inspector came in and he said, hands up all those girls that have got blue ribbon on their hair. I remember I had - couldn\rquote 
t remember you know, my bow was up here somewhere trying to - couldn\rquote t remember what colour, those - those that were quick you know answer - they had marks. I couldn\rquote 
t remember whether my ribbon was blue and was trying to tug at - no, put your hand down, you mustn\rquote t - you had to 
be very quick on - on those - answers. They used to come round and ask all sort - you know, general knowledge questions like that. Never knew they were coming.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Do you know if the boys }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  punished the same way as the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 I think they had th
e same, of course in the junior mixed we were together but the boys, you know, away but no, I - I think the boys had much about the same discipline as the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 In the junior mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes. But of course the girls - they boys, they used to play - cricket and football and that in the playground }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15809763\charrsid8939483 the boys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
 used to get round the - the - my husband used to go to this - round, they were away from us but the playground used to come round and finish like the bottom of this garden and - and I know one of the
 - the class I was in we had a grating and they used to keep coming to the window you know, looking through, peeping through at the girls and they used to get the - teacher used to send notes you know about the boys doing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 They didn\rquote t approve of it you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Report it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 When you were at secondary school age did you mix with the boys at all for anything did you have any lessons with them or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Nothing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 No. We used to go to evening classes when we - little bit older. We used to go - that was the - that was another school, Sal}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15809763\charrsid8939483 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
ers Hill which was about a mile the other way from us. This school, Salters Hill - they were really for more or less the - we were on the borders of Norwood and Dulwich and mo
stly the Dulwich children, borders of Dulwich, they went to Salters Hill and we were this side. We went to Gipsy Road. And - I suppose we were about the - almost the end of, where we were living, the end of the boundary for West Norwood and then two or th
r
ee roads back of us they came into Dulwich you see. And - most of those children went to Salters Hill. But - when we were girls we used to - growing up more or less from - from the girls school we used to come - - be really anxious to get away at half pas
t
 four and rush up that hill, those that had to go that way because when we got to the top of the hill there was the - the bridge, you know tunnel the train went under. Well when we got up there we could run round that way to get home or go straight on. We
ll these boys from Salters Hill school, the used to rush along, they\rquote d have a clothes line and they\rquote d get to the top of this hill and those - oh about a couple of dozen of us girls we had to go that way home and - we\rquote 
d rush up there to get to the top. We got to the top of the bridge and they hadn\rquote t got that far we could run that way round and get away from them, they\rquote d be hiding and they\rquote d get across the road with this clothes line and then we
\rquote d turn to run down the hill and they\rquote d run and they\rquote d gut us in a knot and they\rquote d - they\rquote 
d tie the rope and they used to take us right down to West Norwood and - and untie u at West Norwood station. And we had about two miles to walk home and the trouble we used to get in. Through these boys, but I don\rquote t know, I don\rquote t t
hink our mothers believed it. But - we used to get into trouble because we were late home Ooh, we - I shall never forget those boys. They were - they were a headache.
