\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 But there were such children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes. There were very poor children. Going to school that if you had lunch - you sometimes, you\rquote 
d take a piece of cake or a biscuit or something of that for lunch, not - not very often but they used to look around you know and - with longing. No
, used to say - we were saying the other day, the bad old days as far aw we go, we - I say we that had a comfortable home and not a lot of money and we had a comfortable home and good beds and good parents, we had a lot to be thankful for because, althoug
h they were good days to us }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15809763\charrsid8939483 you\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  get into bed and you\rquote 
d think of all the - the poverty that you had seen around you and it was only the likes of anyone like my mother, I think the - I think the poorer people or the working class people, they helped each ot
her more in those says. I think they tried to help each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Your mother certainly did a lot didn\rquote t she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes. They certainly did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 How old - fourteen. Fourteen. We all let, at fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Would you have stayed longer }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15809763\charrsid8939483 if you\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 If we\rquote d won scholarships. But in those days you - you - your birth month had to come - not that I don\rquote t think - I don
\rquote t think I should ever pass for a scholarship because I was lazy. I used to think, when the lessons were on I was never with it, I was always miles away thinking of when I get home tonight I\rquote 
ll make - what I was going to do, making dolls clothes or something, but I was never with the lessons unless I liked it. The funny thing I lik
ed history, I was all ears for history. I liked needlework afternoons. I liked arithmetic but geography, grammar, anything like that I loathed it. And I was never - never with it. I was always miles away. And - I used to think, oh what - why worry about a
ll this stuff when I grow up I\rquote m going to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14708622 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  and I\rquote 
m going to have lots of children, I imagined them all in - about nine at a time all round the room in cots you see, I - I love children. But - history - history and needlework I used to get - I used to get good marks, always excellent - those }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15809763\charrsid8939483 sorts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  of things. But other things were very poor - poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did your parents take an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Well my - my mother used to be very proud of my specimens of needlework that I used to take home and so was my grandmother, my mother
\rquote s mother, because she was a great needlewoman and - she used to like my samples of needlework that I used to take home and the thing is when I left school I wanted to go in for either millinery or dressmaking. 
And I THINK I could have designed things and that was something that I could shut my eyes and - and visualize making things and I remember the first piece of material I bought, I would be about fifteen I think I paid about sixpence a yard for it and I wen
t
 up into the bedroom and cut out a dress. The only mistake I made, reversing the stuff, I cut two sleeves for one arm and it was the pattern. And you should put, you know, out the pattern together. But - no, my - people put my mother off, they she, oh she
\rquote ll only be - have - if you go dressmaking she\rquote ll be running about with errands, picking up pins and all this sort of thing so I really never had the chance to - to do what I wanted to. And I think it\rquote 
s a great mistake. I think every child should be given what - what they think they\rquote re going to be good at or could do let them do it and if they make a mistake, it doesn\rquote t turn out all right, well you\rquote ve given them their chance. It
\rquote s the same as my - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15809763\charrsid8939483 my sister\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  youngest son, Peter. His frightfully clever with - with -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Do you have any regrets about your education, your school education at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Well the only regrets I have is that - I whish I\rquote d have - been more attentive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15809763\charrsid8939483 Benefited}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  from it? Oh yes, definitely. Oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
You said there were children that were poorer than the others, do you think the teachers singled out some children for better treatment than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, I think the teachers definitely had their favourites. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What particular things made certain children liked more than others do you think, was it anything to do with their backgrounds or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Might have been - might have been their background probably or - I don\rquote t know why because I 
