\insrsid13108354\charrsid8939483 Road}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 , that she used to go to for - he - for all this drink.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 She\rquote d stop while you were out in the car?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, she wasn\rquote t drinking then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 She\rquote d stop while you were out in the car and buy the drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, she probably had - she\rquote d probably have a drink or two before she went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did she actually go into pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 No. No. Always bottles in the house. Oh no, she never went - she - what drink she had - the place was loaded with empty bottles. Ter
rific. I think her husband had a shock when he unearthed all this. Because I told him where to - when my mother took me around there and about this drink and he made out that he didn\rquote 
t know it was going on and I said, well the bottles are all hidden out there, all under the sheets and under - in the drawers and - and clothes all - in boxes, you know, she\rquote d cover them up all over the place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 She must have been so unhappy and he just didn\rquote t want to know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 I - I think he - I think he knew and he just hoped she\rquote d drink herself to death.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 How did he treat you, was he nice to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh yes, quite nice. Yes, quite nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 You weren\rquote t treated as a servant there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no. No, she really treated me as - as a matter of fact I wasn\rquote t too strong r
eally and it - I think mother must have got me this little job through, the Shrubsall children started going to school, that\rquote s right, they started going to school and - I think mother must have got me this through Mrs Cooper, I can\rquote 
t remember how I got it 
but I do remember going there and - I was very fond of Mrs Ruthen, she treated me as though I was her daughter. I wore just the clothes I wanted to wear, there was no dis - you know, sort of having to wear - certain clothes and - I just helped her in the 
house, it\rquote s more - almost, you might say, she almost }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13108354\charrsid8939483 adopted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  me.
