\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you have breakfast together in the morning or did he have something and then go off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no, we always had breakfast together. Well as a matter of fact he used to be on different }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13108354\charrsid8939483 duties}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  you see, some - some times
 he was in the reference - reference rooms in the mornings from time it opened until certain hour in the afternoon, and then some weeks he would go on duty at two o\rquote 
clock in the afternoon and be in the reference room until after nine at night, until the reference room close you see. That\rquote s upstairs, the reference room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What did he do for food when he was there \lquote til after nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Well we\rquote d have - we\rquote d have a midday meal you see and he\rquote d }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13108354\charrsid8939483 go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  probably about two o\rquote clock and then very often if the evening was nice I\rquote d go and meet him, we\rquote d walk home and - and we\rquote 
d have supper. And of course, in those days you - you had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13108354\charrsid8939483 marvellous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  fish shop. You - you, very often you had fish and chips. }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13108354\charrsid8939483 Do you know, you may not believe this but when we were young, if we had a penny given to us we could go to the fish shop and we could buy a - a little piece of fish, ha\rquote penny and a ha
\rquote porth of chips and now the amount that we had of that for one penny, when we came home on Saturday evening, we\rquote re a bit hungry, we had sandwiches you see and cups of coffee all day, travelling all day, I - I - we hadn\rquote 
t had fish and chips for a long time so I said to Pip, well let\rquote s get in the car and go down to Walton and get some fish and chips. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 And I said I wanted fish and chips for two. Well
 that came to five shillings, there was two potions, half a crown each you see, fish and chi-s. Well I said, one would never believe that we bought that amount for a penny when we were children. You see, your generation, they look and they think, oh must 
