Oh well such as - what we used to do is to buy a joint on Saturday, mind you get a joint for - lovely joint for half a crown. And that lasted you until Tuesday. Now I probably buy a joint and I roast that on Sunday with - Yorkshire puddi
ng and roast potatoes and everything and then - I would make sufficient gravy so that that was left over and - then on Monday I would make another little Yorkshire pudding and - and roast potatoes and - greenstuff and then I would cut the meat up and just
 lay it in the gravy, pop it in the oven to just warm it through and we\rquote d have another hot dinner. And then on Tuesday - it\rquote d probably be sufficient to have a cold meal. Cold meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What would you do the rest of the week?
