, well if I had a half a crown left on Monday and I had sufficient - food to go - meat and things in the house until Tuesday, that half a crown would see me because I - I never - I had my money once a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13108354\charrsid8939483 month}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  and I just put the thirty shillings for each week you see and I wouldn\rquote t touch that thirty shilling until the next month - \lquote 
til the next weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 You always shopped by the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What sort of food would you have on the other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Then - then perhaps - on Wednesday, you could buy liver for fourpence a - pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 You were saying that a rasher of bacon would work out at about three farthings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 About - threepence for two rashers you might say and you might say tuppence for the liver and it\rquote 
d be fivepence. And you could get cabbages for about a ha\rquote penny each and a penny each would last you two days, so that - really and truly you - you had - a good meal, then you\rquote 
d make a pudding, probably stewed apples or rice pudding and that would last you two days. If you had a half, mind 
you I used to buy the - the bulk of my shopping on the weekend whereby butter and - sugar and tea and everything and - grocery - greengrocery things to last the week, all that. But if I had half crown left on - on Monday that would buy - probably liver an
d bacon one day, some fish another day, that was about fourpence a pound and - there was quite sufficient money in half a crown to go through the rest of the - the rest of the week. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13108354\charrsid8939483 
Another thing you would buy was - scrag of mutton, we used to call it scrag of mutton which - and then there\rquote s the best end of mutton comes from that, used to buy scrag of mutton for threepence a pound so that - if you had two pound of scrag you
\rquote d make a nice stew for two days, just for -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
