Oh yes. Were very friendly. As a matter of fact - just before the war broke - when we went there, the Mrs Fox she had a little baby girl, Mavis - Maisie she called her and she was about - a year old I suppose. No, she wasn\rquote t a year old, she was qu
ite young. And it was said she was expecting another baby because it was the - the war broke out, yes, we\rquote d only been there a few months and she had this little girl and she was in the - January, that\rquote 
s right, she had a baby in the January and the December, that would be about ten months, no, nearly a year wouldn\rquote 
t it - eleven months, and she was expecting another baby in the February and my husband was on - it was his afternoon late duty and Mrs Fox was taken ill and I was in the house alone and she called
 up, she was - you know, feeling not well and I had to go for - for nurse and this baby was born and only lived two hours and I was up all night. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 
You know, when it was born - No, anyhow the nurse came, she was - she was in labour and - and she was a terrib
le panic so I was up - it was born early hours of the morning, her husband had his own business in Holborn and it was picture framing, all that, and - he very often never got home until one o\rquote 
clock in the morning, they used to very, very late hours working and - I was up making - ironing and airing and getting these babies clothes you see already, she hadn\rquote t anything ready. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 So - anyhow the baby was born, it lived two hours. And when it was born they took - the nurse - would you like to come down and see the baby? And it\rquote 
s face was like - not much bigger than that, about the size of an orange. And I suppose the smell of the room, I just went off in a faint. I just passed out. And really it was too much for - it was really. And the baby was such - a little tin
y thing, it lived two hours and died. But - I stayed up the whole night and my husband - and when it was born early hours of the morning and - that was that. And I was alone when it - in all this - when she was taken bad.
