\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 You weren\rquote t living at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 1914. No, I hadn\rquote t left my flat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 I thought perhaps you\rquote d gone home to help look after the house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 The war broke out in the August so I went home, shut the flat and my husband came - when he\rquote 
d finished duty at the library he used to come to Norwood. My mother was away for a fortnight. They\rquote 
d booked their holiday for the September you see, war broke out and - my brothers - my eldest brother volunteered, he was in the Territorials like my husband, he was with him. They were away at a c
amp with - my eldest brother when the war broke out and they asked for volunteers for - for service abroad and he volunteered, so - that was in the August. Mum and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 daddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 , they - they went for their holiday in September and I said I would go and look after the house because I had these sisters at home, un}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14708622 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 , and - and this brother who was working, had been working since the previous January you might say. And - no, we stayed home then until my mother and father came back from their holiday. Then we went
 back to Brixton to our flat. That was in September. Then in the December my husband joined up. And in the December - after he joined up I moved to a flat in - Dulwich, Carnick Street. Oh it came under West Norwood, yes, because round the corner was Dulwi
ch, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 Carnick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  Street, West Norwood. I was - my brother in-law, my sister\rquote 
s husband, they were builders and undertakers, they lived in a - next door to this Mrs Gotch where I had the flat and - and his family had this - shop and undertakers and builders and th
ey - they were next door. Well round that corner, that was Dulwich. Then I had a flat there. Now exactly a flat, I had - two rooms and the use of the kitchen and the bathroom and that. But my husband wanted me - he joined up, he wanted me to be near my pa
rents. He didn\rquote t want to leave me at Brixton and all I could get was these - two rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Were you there when you received the news?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 I was there when my husband was killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 That\rquote s where you got the letters you were telling me about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 After that what did you do, did you go home to your parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 No. I stayed there. I stayed there until I was - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14708622 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Was it after you heard the news that you got this job working in the Australian Headquarters? Or was that before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 No, when - when my husband joined up and I went back to Norwood they were doing - the church people were - they had a room in Norwood, I
\rquote ve forgotten just where, women where at the bottom of - near the station and it was Mr Bright the organist 
of the church he - he - he had this - contract for so many T.N.T. cases they were making, they were sort of little rubber - like rubber, very fine and then we had a long stick about that length, it\rquote 
s round, like a stick of rock you might say, and - and we had these - these T.N.T. cases that was for the T.N.T. powder and - and we had to do the finest of stitching, we had to make these and then there was a little cap when we - when we\rquote 
d sewn them up, two rows of sewing, all very fine sewing, and then when we\rquote 
d sewn those up, they were like that and about that length then we used to put a little round cap, they were little round caps about the size of that, we used to put them over - over this stick and then pull these things over, used to be about like that -
 that\rquote s how they were to go over the stick you see, we\rquote 
d pull those over the stick and then when it got on the level with the top we used to do fine oversewing the tops of those and then about so far down we had to go all the way round there stitching and then they used to come out about that length, cases. }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
And they were filled with T.N.T. powder. And you - for a hundred you had three and something a hundred. Very very fine sewing, very trying for the eyes. Well we did that for a while and then - then from t
hat - from there - they - they were do - we went to London. We were doing them there over - Bourne and Hollingsworth. We had a room over Bourne and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 Hollingsworth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  and there\rquote s quite a lot of this war work went on there. And I was there. For - for some time and then from that I went to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 Australian}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  headquarters, clerical work. And - and then from - from the - when the war finished - I went to the Ministry of Pensions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 When did you first start doing the work with the T.N.T. cases?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Ah as soon as - you might -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Before your husband went off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 
Oh no. After he went. I think about 19 - he - he went in 19 - December 1914 and I think I started somewhere about - I started the beginning of \rquote 15 and then I was only doing that for about three months the
n my husband came down to Frinton. In training. And I came down to Frinton and he was training here for about nine months and I stayed in a little cottage where he was billeted in Wickward Lane. And then - of course then he went - off from there and I wen
t back again and I did more war - war work you see. And then when I had a chance perhaps go for a weekend and that I used to just go - Winchester and places like that and Bank Holidays and that - wherever he was and he could fix me up somewhere I\rquote 
d go and stay. The last place was Winchester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 When you were doing the T.N.T. cases to start with that was in West Norwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 What hours did you work, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh I think we worked practically - all day. You\rquote d say from nine o\rquote clock - or what time you could - you could put in. I don
\rquote t think we were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 You were paid by piecework were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 By piecework. Whatever hours you could do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you go there every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 I did that every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Saturdays too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 I don\rquote t think we worked Saturdays. We may have done but I\rquote ve forgotten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 When you were working at the Ministry of Pensions that was clerical work too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Was that the last job you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 That was the last job I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Did you ever belong to any sort of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 trade}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  union in any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Never anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 When you were working in your earlier jobs did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9192541\charrsid8939483 feel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483  that employers and workers and different outlooks, different sort of interests or didn\rquote t you think about that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10690358 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 Well I - no, I don\rquote t think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5390660 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16204869\charrsid8939483 In your work with the T.N.T. cases there wouldn\rquote t have been a division, it wasn\rquote 
t like craftsmen and labourers and that kind of thing there was it, you just mixed with other girls?
